1_1Ci5Y4TxZwY1SQhvQR7Ttbdyyai4WRV5TU.body:
I have a file, `/opt/zeronet/zeronetd`, that basically reads
```sh
#!/bin/bash
cd /opt/zeronet || {
  echo 'cannot cd to /opt/zeronet' >&2
  exit 1
}
exec -a zeronetd python2 zeronet.py
```
and then a `ExecStart=/opt/zeronet/zeronetd` in the `zeronet.service` file. Works for me.
